        <div class="commenttext"><p>Cyprus inspired biz journalists to postulate how citizens could have avoided tax confiscation had their currency been extra-governmental, bringing it to the attention of millions of business-minded people.  BitCoin cannot be confiscated by anyone.  It can&#8217;t be regulated by anyone.  The demand for such a currency increased while the supply can only be increased by mining, a slow and expensive process, so the price of existing coin goes up.  Way up.</p>
