        <a href ="http://singularityhub.com/?author=15206"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/3eb028f72b0fbd49791f267c3237ab06?s=96&amp;d=monsterid&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-96 photo' height='96' width='96' /></a>           
    </div>
    <div class="comment-right" >
                            <a href="http://singularityhub.com/?author=15206"><cite class="fn">thadster</cite> <span class="says">says:</span></a>
                           			       
        <div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://singularityhub.com/2013/04/09/bitcoin-blows-up-exchange-rate-jumps-ten-fold-in-recent-weeks/#comment-63595">
        April 9, 2013 at 2:09 pm</a>        </div>

        <div class="commenttext"><p>It&#8217;s likely a supply demand problem.  There is only so much value to be had, and Bitcoins are a great way to move money around without a lot of attention from other governments/currencies, so it&#8217;s a good tool for capital flight.  There&#8217;s a real risk to having a currency not backed by sovereignty, and price volatility is built into the mix because supply is fixed and demand is not.  </p>
<p>I agree it&#8217;s a good test of the future of money, but it isn&#8217;t the future of money.</p>
</div>

        <div class="reply">
        <a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2013/04/09/bitcoin-blows-up-exchange-rate-jumps-ten-fold-in-recent-weeks/?replytocom=63595#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-63595", "63595", "respond", "60547")'>Reply</a>        </div>
