	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-dobermanmacleod even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-63619">
		<div id="div-comment-63619" class="comment-body ">
	    <div class="comment-left">
        <a href ="http://singularityhub.com/?author=3604"><img alt='' src='https://graph.facebook.com/1433678215/picture?type=large' class='avatar avatar-96 photo' height='96' width='96' /></a>           
    </div>
    <div class="comment-right" >
                            <a href="http://singularityhub.com/?author=3604"><cite class="fn">dobermanmacleod</cite> <span class="says">says:</span></a>
                           			       
        <div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://singularityhub.com/2013/04/09/bitcoin-blows-up-exchange-rate-jumps-ten-fold-in-recent-weeks/#comment-63619">
        April 9, 2013 at 9:30 pm</a>        </div>

        <div class="commenttext"><p>The question of the conception of currency is too hard for most people to grasp.  I&#8217;ve found that an audio clip from the audio book &#8220;Atlas Shrugged&#8221; where Francisco d&#8217;Anconia expounds on the idea that money is the root of all evil.  Money is simply a medium that enables the trading of goods and services.</p>
<p>Furthermore, many people have a hard time swallowing the Federal Reserve setup, where a private corporation has complete control of the US money supply.  Bitcoin is just another wrinkle, where the &#8220;e-currency&#8221; enables commerce to take place, and the currency takes on a weird value of it&#8217;s own, rather than as a means to an end.</p>
</div>

